Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> program
Rule 1     program -> statements
Rule 2     statements -> statement
Rule 3     statements -> statements statement
Rule 4     statement -> if_statement SEMICOLON
Rule 5     if_statement -> condition QUESTION assign_statement
Rule 6     if_statement -> condition QUESTION if_statement
Rule 7     assign_statement -> ASSIGN variable expression
Rule 8     condition -> expression EQ expression
Rule 9     condition -> expression NEQ expression
Rule 10    condition -> expression LT expression
Rule 11    condition -> expression GT expression
Rule 12    expression -> expression MINUS expression
Rule 13    expression -> expression POWER
Rule 14    expression -> LPAREN expression RPAREN
Rule 15    expression -> NUMBER
Rule 16    expression -> variable
Rule 17    variable -> IDENTIFIER
Rule 18    variable -> IDENTIFIER LBRACKET NUMBER RBRACKET

Terminals, with rules where they appear

ASSIGN               : 7
EQ                   : 8
GT                   : 11
IDENTIFIER           : 17 18
LBRACKET             : 18
LPAREN               : 14
LT                   : 10
MINUS                : 12
NEQ                  : 9
NUMBER               : 15 18
POWER                : 13
QUESTION             : 5 6
RBRACKET             : 18
RPAREN               : 14
SEMICOLON            : 4
error                : 

